 The Maritime Workers Union of Nigeria, (MWUN) yesterday said it would resist any attempt by employers in the nation’s maritime industry to retrench or slash salaries of workers under the guise of negative effect of COVID-19 pandemic. The workers cautioned that such move will be counter productive, saying that employers should instead be thinking of increasing salaries and allowances of workers to cope with consequences of COVID-19. This came as MWUN, in collaboration with International Transport Federation, ITF, presented Personal Protective Equipment, PPE,  to seafarers  across the nation’s seaports as Nigeria today joins the rest of the world to mark the world Seafarers, Day. At the commencement of the distribution of PPE, president general of MWUN, Prince Adewale Adeyanju, contended that no reasonable employer  should contemplate any retrenchment or salary slash in this  difficult period of COVID-19. 